A History of American Painting (Praeger World of Art)
Praeger Publishers | 1971 | ISBN 1112823549 | English | 292 pages | PDF | 32 MB

In this readable, intelligent survey, the history of American painting is traced from its origins as a provincial offshoot of the European Baroque to its international triumph in the second half of the twentieth century. Filled with both color and black & white photos
